(1) Elon Musk=E2=80=99s Neuralink Shows First Patient Using Its Brain Impla=
nt [ https://substack.com/redirect/c80a2215-891a-4fe3-a270-0eb8aa79cd1b?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Rolfe Winkler [ https://substack.com/redirect/37ac1589-0722-48b4-8b63-1d1f1=
c5273e6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU =
] and Alexa Corse [ https://substack.com/redirect/14d2951c-aec7-4328-8c39-1=
1a9e2c226c8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ] for The Wall Street Journal
Nueralink introduced its first patient to the world yesterday. 29-year-old =
Noland Arbaugh, who lost all movement beneath his shoulders after a 2016 ac=
cident, received Nueralink=E2=80=99s first brain-computer chip implant a fe=
w months ago.=20
In the live video, Noland played chess on his computer and moved his cursor=
 around, notably while talking to the interviewer and engaging the audience=
 on other topics. Arbaugh described the sensation by saying it felt like =
=E2=80=9Cusing the force on a cursor.=E2=80=9D
Brain-computer chips have been around for over 20 years, but Nueralink=E2=
=80=99s display was novel for two main reasons. First, Nueralink=E2=80=99s =
device transmits data wirelessly, meaning its mobile and not clunked down b=
y wires. Second, Neuralink=E2=80=99s chip allows for a certain level of mul=
ti-tasking (playing chess telekinetically while speaking about surgery for =
example) that is indistinguishable from how a =E2=80=9Cnormal=E2=80=9D brai=
n works.
Say what you want about Musk, but the guy delivers. For those taking notes =
at home, over the past two weeks, he:
Launched the largest flying object ever into orbit with SpaceX,
Introduced the most sophisticated brain-computer interface ever with Neural=
ink,
Released Full Self Driving v12.3 in Tesla cars,
Open sourced xAI=E2=80=99s foundation model, Grok,
Continued to shitpost on his public square toy, X.=20
Elon tweeted that Blindsight is next for Neuralink [ https://substack.com/r=
