</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><em>Saahil Desai for The Atlantic</em></p><b=
lockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; padding:=
 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>Direct File isn&#8217;t=
 perfect&#8212;the program is available in only </span><a href=3D"https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/c819aeba-a34a-446a-b17b-bc2578484e89?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(=
54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">12 states</a><span>, and it isn&#=
8217;t able to handle anything beyond the simplest tax situations&#8212;but=
 it&#8217;s a glimpse of a world where government tech benefits millions of=
 Americans. In turn, it is also an agonizing realization of how far we are =
from that reality.</span></em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Fun little=
 reminder here: Tax Day is 24 days away. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Tax Da=
y is important because its the day during which the government compels its =
citizens to pay (always surprisingly high) taxes in order to fund things li=
ke the aforementioned $8.5 billion Intel/Arizona grant. For years, it&#8217=
;s been even </span><em>more</em><span> fun thanks to services like TurboTa=
x. TurboTax is a product from Intuit, a private corporation that offers a v=
ariety of individual and SMB financial products and for years has been lobb=
ying Washington to keep the process of filing taxes asininely complex. Why =
would Intuit do such a thing?</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Because if it&#82=
17;s hard and scary to file taxes, then the 150M+ Americans that need to fi=
le taxes each year will turn to TurboTax to help them do it. Let&#8217;s sa=
y the average TurboTax customer pays $100 per year. That $15 billion of swe=
et, high margin government-forced ARR up for grabs. And if it&#8217;s even =
harder and scarier, then customers will be convinced into purchasing upsell=
 products and consultations. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The other fun part comes=
 a few weeks later, when the IRS tells you that you actually messed up and =
didn&#8217;t pay the right amount, which it turns out they knew all along, =
but Intuit&#8217;s lobbyists asked them to make you try to guess anyway jus=
t for funsies. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The thing is&#8230;filing taxes should=
n&#8217;t be that hard and complex. If the IRS knows, you should be able to=
 work directly with the IRS, online, if you so choose. </p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>Enter Direct File. Direct File is a new pilot tax filing service in=
troduced by the IRS to allow eligible taxpayers to file their taxes online =
for free, directly with the IRS. It&#8217;s designed for simplicity, is off=
ered in English and Spanish, and supported by mobile-first real-time online=
 support from IRS customer service representatives&#8230;who don&#8217;t ha=
ve the incentive to upsell you on a bunch of products. It&#8217;s now avail=
able in </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/0e0203c5-db68-483c-=
bd78-ca20874034b7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;=
">12 states</a><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Don&#8217;t get me wrong=
, I am all for private businesses offering services that complement governm=
ent services &#8212; that&#8217;s in part what makes the American economy s=
o dynamic &#8212; but not when incentives are totally out of whack. The inc=
entives around tax filing have been totally out of whack thanks to regulato=
ry capture. So it&#8217;s great to see the government step up and offer a m=
odern alternative.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Bonus</strong></p><p style=
